                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/177: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-17T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 17, 1929—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>251. Section 1 of your 274 has just arrived. Please do not under any
                    circumstances consent to the proposed invitation being sent until we have had an
                    opportunity to receive it and state our views. The President and I have serious
                    objections to even the portion contained in this first section, and we think
                    that the invitation itself had much better await the conclusion of Mr.
                    MacDonald’s visit. I will give you our matured views after receipt of the
                    remainder of the proposed invitation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
